QReadLine â€” A drop-in replacement for QLineEdit

QReadLine is a one line input widget for Qt (http://www.qtsoftware.com/) It is
based on QLineEdit (http://doc.trolltech.com/4.5/qlineedit.html) and extends
it with emacs-like key bindings. 

The latest source is available through git with:

    git clone http://www.wiktory.org/~sol/code/cg1.git/

API documentation is at:

    http://www.wiktory.org/~sol/code/qreadline_doc/

QReadLine is free software, see LICENSE for details. Please make sure that you
comply with the licensing terms of Qt Software when linking this software with
Qt.
